the front end,

00:42:49.780 --> 00:42:51.440
back end networking layer.

00:42:51.440 --> 00:42:52.680
So in Reflex,

00:42:52.680 --> 00:42:53.700
you'll never have to write

00:42:53.700 --> 00:42:54.660
an API call.

00:42:54.660 --> 00:42:55.440
You never have to write

00:42:55.440 --> 00:42:56.100
a post request,

00:42:56.100 --> 00:42:56.820
a get request,

00:42:56.820 --> 00:42:58.440
or any of that.

00:42:58.440 --> 00:42:59.100
All of that is done

00:42:59.100 --> 00:42:59.680
under the hood.

00:43:00.120 --> 00:43:01.520
So to set up

00:43:01.520 --> 00:43:03.720
your kind of state

00:43:03.720 --> 00:43:04.320
and interactive,

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:05.660
you can do this all

00:43:05.660 --> 00:43:06.480
within what we call

00:43:06.480 --> 00:43:07.460
a state class.

00:43:07.460 --> 00:43:08.820
So a state class

00:43:08.820 --> 00:43:10.360
is just a normal Python class

00:43:10.360 --> 00:43:11.040
and within it,

00:43:11.040 --> 00:43:12.660
you define all the fields

00:43:12.660 --> 00:43:13.240
in your state

00:43:13.240 --> 00:43:14.500
that can change over time,

00:43:14.500 --> 00:43:16.420
which we call vars,

00:43:16.420 --> 00:43:19.620
as well as any event handlers

00:43:19.620 --> 00:43:22.360
that can change the vars.

00:43:22.360 --> 00:43:23.360
So an event handler

00:43:23.360 --> 00:43:24.080
is just a Python

00:43:24.080 --> 00:43:25.300
like function or method.

00:43:25.300 --> 00:43:27.020
And I think the image gen

00:43:27.020 --> 00:43:27.980
is a good example of it.

00:43:27.980 --> 00:43:28.680
So for example,

00:43:28.820 --> 00:43:29.540
in the image gen,

00:43:29.540 --> 00:43:31.240
the image URL is a var

00:43:31.240 --> 00:43:31.860
because it's something

00:43:31.860 --> 00:43:32.680
that's going to change.

00:43:32.680 --> 00:43:34.060
And an event handler

00:43:34.060 --> 00:43:36.980
would be the get image function,

00:43:36.980 --> 00:43:38.400
which is a function

00:43:38.400 --> 00:43:39.840
that when they hit submit

00:43:39.840 --> 00:43:40.540
on the input,

00:43:40.540 --> 00:43:42.100
we call it.

00:43:42.100 --> 00:43:43.380
So in order to hook up

00:43:43.380 --> 00:43:44.300
the front end and back end,

00:43:44.300 --> 00:43:45.060
all you have to do

00:43:45.060 --> 00:43:47.480
is hook up the UI

00:43:47.480 --> 00:43:48.680
to the Python function.

00:43:48.680 --> 00:43:49.360
So you can say

00:43:49.360 --> 00:43:50.480
button on click

00:43:50.480 --> 00:43:52.840
equals state dot get image.

00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:54.240
And what this does

00:43:54.240 --> 00:43:54.920
under the hood

00:43:54.920 --> 00:43:56.700
is when you click that button,

00:43:56.700 --> 00:43:58.580
it creates an event.

00:43:58.660 --> 00:43:59.140
it sends up

00:43:59.140 --> 00:43:59.900
through a WebSocket

00:43:59.900 --> 00:44:00.720
to the back end.

00:44:00.720 --> 00:44:02.280
It will run your Python function

00:44:02.280 --> 00:44:03.160
on the back end.

00:44:03.160 --> 00:44:04.420
So whether that's

00:44:04.420 --> 00:44:04.860
your OpenAI,

00:44:04.860 --> 00:44:05.360
your replicate,

00:44:05.360 --> 00:44:06.120
whatever it is,

00:44:06.120 --> 00:44:08.360
all their state

00:44:08.360 --> 00:44:09.320
runs on the back end

00:44:09.320 --> 00:44:09.800
on the server.

00:44:09.800 --> 00:44:10.780
And that's what allows us

00:44:10.780 --> 00:44:11.360
to keep the state

00:44:11.360 --> 00:44:12.080
in pure Python.

00:44:12.080 --> 00:44:14.020
So it will update

00:44:14.020 --> 00:44:15.880
your state UI.

00:44:15.880 --> 00:44:16.600
In this case,

00:44:16.600 --> 00:44:17.160
it's going to update

00:44:17.160 --> 00:44:17.880
the image URL

00:44:17.880 --> 00:44:19.600
and send that back.

00:44:19.600 --> 00:44:20.160
And it works

00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:21.820
very similar to React

00:44:21.820 --> 00:44:22.420
in the sense that

00:44:22.420 --> 00:44:23.540
as your state updates,

00:44:23.540 --> 00:44:24.400
the front end

00:44:24.400 --> 00:44:25.280
updates reactively.

