00:45:24.860 --> 00:45:26.380
often need to make

00:45:26.380 --> 00:45:27.140
a bunch of requests.

00:45:27.140 --> 00:45:28.860
So rather than having

00:45:28.860 --> 00:45:30.020
to reestablish

00:45:30.020 --> 00:45:31.180
a new HTTP request

00:45:31.180 --> 00:45:31.680
every time,

00:45:31.680 --> 00:45:33.120
by keeping a WebSocket,

00:45:33.120 --> 00:45:33.900
we are really able

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:34.420
to optimize

00:45:34.420 --> 00:45:35.400
the speed of the apps.

00:45:35.400 --> 00:45:36.900
So when you create,

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:38.460
